               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421024-name-1255" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1255" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1255" type="surname" value="LEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1255" type="given" value="RICHARD BREWER"></interp>RICHARD BREWER LEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a seaman, lodging at Mr. Boyle's, in White Horse-place. On the 21st of October I went up stairs to lay down after dinner—I had a paper containing four sovereigns—I pot them into my fob—when I went to bed no one was in the room—when I awoke I missed my sovereigns.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421024-name-1256" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1256" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1256" type="surname" value="BOYLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1256" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES BOYLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep this house—the prosecutor bad been drink<lb></lb>ing, and went to lay down—the prisoner lodged there, and he went up stairs to lay down too—he came down again in a quarter of an hour—no one else went up during that time—the prisoner said he would go out and buy a bit of soap, and a pint of half-and-half—I said he had only 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., which I had let him have in the morning—soon after I heard the pro<lb></lb>secutor had been robbed—I went after the prisoner, and found him in the King William, treating a young woman with brandy-and-water—I followed him to a baker's-shop next door, and saw him counting his money—there was 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and some other money, which I thought was two farthings, in a paper—I got him home with a great deal of trouble—he was very abusive—I examined the paper, and found it had two so<lb></lb>vereigns in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421024-name-1257" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1257" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1257" type="surname" value="RANSOM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421024-name-1257" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN RANSOM</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 328.) I went to the house—I saw Boyle and the prisoner behind him—I held my lamp in the direction of the prisoner's legs, and he dropped a piece of paper—Mr. Boyle picked it up, and it contained two sovereigns—he gave the prisoner in charge.</p>
